The paper deals with the problem of learning face models from weakly-labelled images collected from the web, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves iterative pruning of data based on discriminativeness and representativeness, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of query-based image retrieval (cs.IR) and benchmark datasets (cs.MM), which are common in computer vision research. Finally, the paper involves classification of faces, which is a task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
